    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>DVD SOFTWARE TRIAL ENDS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Amy Harmon</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Harmon, Amy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Trial in federal case that tests limits of Hollywood's control over its digital properties ends as Judge Lewis A Kaplan tells lawyers that he is impressed with testimony from defense witness as to why computer software code should be protected by First Amendment; eight movie studios have urged Kaplan to stop a Web site operator from distributing software program that unscrambles encryption on DVD movie discs (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The trial in a federal case that tests the limits of Hollywood's control over its digital properties ended yesterday as Judge Lewis A. Kaplan told lawyers he had been impressed with testimony from a defense witness as to why computer software code should be protected by the First Amendment. Eight movie studios have urged the judge to stop a Web site operator from distributing a software program that unscrambles the encryption on DVD movie discs. Judge Kaplan ordered attorneys to submit their final briefs in the case by August 8. They may reconvene for closing arguments later this week.</p>
        <p>Amy Harmon (NYT)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The trial in a federal case that tests the limits of Hollywood's control over its digital properties ended yesterday as Judge Lewis A. Kaplan told lawyers he had been impressed with testimony from a defense witness as to why computer software code should be protected by the First Amendment. Eight movie studios have urged the judge to stop a Web site operator from distributing a software program that unscrambles the encryption on DVD movie discs. Judge Kaplan ordered attorneys to submit their final briefs in the case by August 8. They may reconvene for closing arguments later this week.</p>
        <p>Amy Harmon (NYT)</p>
